13:24.150 --> 13:25.833
Okay.

13:25.890 --> 13:27.881
Let's go for it.

13:42.600 --> 13:44.818
[indistinct chatter,
phones ringing]

13:47.040 --> 13:49.031
[wheels squeaking,
cart rattling]

13:53.830 --> 13:55.081
Hey.

13:55.130 --> 13:57.348
Hey.

13:57.400 --> 13:58.742
Oh, why so down?

13:58.790 --> 14:01.964
Turn that frown
upside down.Go to hell.

14:02.010 --> 14:03.784
You're very cheerful.

14:03.840 --> 14:05.535
I'm liking it here.

14:07.230 --> 14:09.278
I need an office.

14:09.320 --> 14:10.491
This is crazy.

14:10.540 --> 14:12.405
Take that one.

14:12.460 --> 14:14.496
I can't just take an office.Sure you can.

14:14.540 --> 14:15.882
Hey.You're gonna
get me fired.

14:15.940 --> 14:17.896
Hey.What's going on?

14:17.940 --> 14:19.237
We want to steal an office.

14:19.290 --> 14:20.894
I thought you were out
grand jurying.

14:20.940 --> 14:22.248
Tomorrow. They delayed it.

14:22.290 --> 14:23.507
Uh, what do you mean,
steal an office?

14:23.550 --> 14:24.812
I told her
she should take

14:24.860 --> 14:26.248
that one.Well, whose is it?

14:26.300 --> 14:27.904
Lucca's.No.

14:27.950 --> 14:29.383
No one's.[phone rings]

14:29.430 --> 14:31.034
Lucca Quinn.

14:32.300 --> 14:34.427
[sighing]:
Okay. On my way up.

14:35.740 --> 14:38.436
The gun shop bookkeeping.

14:38.480 --> 14:40.129
Don't move me.

14:44.310 --> 14:47.928
[quietly]:
She's not happy, is she?Not much.

14:47.970 --> 14:50.575
We came in as peers,
and I get the office,

14:50.620 --> 14:52.622
she gets the cubicle.Right.

14:52.670 --> 14:53.887
I need to hire you
freelance.

14:53.930 --> 14:56.535
Is this another subject?Yes.

14:56.590 --> 14:57.932
It's something personal.

14:57.980 --> 14:59.709
Your husband?No, my daughter.

14:59.760 --> 15:02.149
Oh, my God.
My family needs

15:02.200 --> 15:04.543
a full-time investigator--
that's not normal, is it?

15:04.590 --> 15:06.023
Sure it is.

15:06.070 --> 15:07.549
What's the issue?

15:07.600 --> 15:09.465
Have you ever heard
of a software

15:09.510 --> 15:12.638
called genuinethought.com?

15:13.690 --> 15:16.602
Her business is up almost 20%

15:16.650 --> 15:19.562
year to date.So good, there are no damages.

15:19.610 --> 15:22.431
CARY: She'll say her business
would be up even more--
gun business is booming.

15:22.480 --> 15:25.267
I agree-- they're trying
to make an example out of this.

15:25.310 --> 15:27.619
Take on the gun industry
and we'll make you pay.

15:27.660 --> 15:31.744
I wish I could sue for
how much money I've
lost on my business.

15:31.800 --> 15:33.665
What do you mean?

15:33.710 --> 15:35.621
My motel.

15:35.670 --> 15:37.752
Every time there's a new story
about the gun violence,

15:37.800 --> 15:40.792
I lose reservations.LUCCA: Well,
why can't you try to recover?

15:40.850 --> 15:43.148
CARY: No. The Protection of
Lawful Commerce in Arms Act

15:43.200 --> 15:45.236
is the problem-- it makes
it impossible to recover

15:45.290 --> 15:48.589
against anyone in
the gun industry.No one has tried civil claims

15:48.640 --> 15:50.028
tied to tourism.

15:51.820 --> 15:54.459
So, y... I'm sorry, what?

15:54.510 --> 15:56.683
We are countersuing
for damages, Your Honor.

15:56.730 --> 15:59.198
Really? How does thatwork?Your Honor, did you want to know

15:59.260 --> 16:00.420
how that works?I do, thank you.

16:00.480 --> 16:02.345
The plaintiff here
can't show losses.

16:04.780 --> 16:06.429
But our client can.

16:06.480 --> 16:08.744
Mr. Dargis owns a motel
in the neighborhood,

16:08.790 --> 16:12.521
and his losses are directly
related to the increase
in gun Violence.

16:12.580 --> 16:15.094
Excuse me, but congress has
made this kind of lawsuit

16:15.140 --> 16:16.448
impossible.

16:16.490 --> 16:18.401
The Protection
of Lawful Commerce...

16:18.450 --> 16:19.576
CARY:
PLCAA

16:19.630 --> 16:20.790
contains exceptions,
one of which

16:20.840 --> 16:23.491
is the Predicate
Statute Exception.

16:23.540 --> 16:26.327
_If Gloria's Guns' activities
Violated another eXIsting law,

16:26.370 --> 16:28.065
her immunity
is stripped.

16:28.110 --> 16:30.021
And what statute
did she violate?

16:30.070 --> 16:31.321
The Illinois Promotion Act.

