What is that?

16:33.810 --> 16:35.539
An act of the legislature

16:35.600 --> 16:37.374
promoting tourism.20 ILCS

16:37.430 --> 16:38.772
665 declares that

16:38.820 --> 16:41.516
the state must increase
the economic impact

16:41.560 --> 16:43.425
of tourism
throughout the state.

16:43.480 --> 16:45.516
This is a joke.No, this is a law.

16:45.560 --> 16:48.438
Gloria's sale of
thousands of crime guns

16:48.480 --> 16:51.210
undermines tourism,
and our client_ has
a tourism busmess

16:51.270 --> 16:53.044
that is suffering.Your Honor,

16:53.090 --> 16:55.911
the Federal courts have ruled
that the statute

16:55.970 --> 16:58.700
must be directly applicable
to firearms.Not all.

16:58.750 --> 17:01.401
And circuit splits
are exactly what bubbles up

17:01.450 --> 17:02.883
to the Supreme Court.

17:02.930 --> 17:04.443
_ Illinois needs
its own gUIdance

17:04.500 --> 17:05.888
on this issue.Okay!

17:05.930 --> 17:08.398
You had me at
Supreme Court.

17:08.460 --> 17:10.018
ABERNATHY:
Counselors, let's make some law.

17:10.070 --> 17:11.583
_ Come on back
With your arguments,

17:11.630 --> 17:13.370
and we'll contend.[bangs gavel]

17:14.720 --> 17:16.324
Good day in court?

17:16.380 --> 17:17.938
Uh, yes, actually.

17:17.990 --> 17:19.685
You're not drinking?

17:19.730 --> 17:21.504
I'm trying to go easier.

17:21.560 --> 17:23.073
Well...

17:23.120 --> 17:25.588
to going easier.

17:26.740 --> 17:29.038
Have you, uh, given
it more thought?

17:29.090 --> 17:32.730
An all-female firm?Al| female name partners.

17:35.310 --> 17:37.744
I don't want to hurt Cary.

17:37.790 --> 17:39.610
Well, you won't
be doing anything.

17:39.660 --> 17:41.833
I will offer to buy him out.

17:41.880 --> 17:44.667
But what if he doesn't want
to be bought out?

17:45.970 --> 17:47.574
Then we'll talk.

17:48.930 --> 17:50.625
I wouldn't
be doing this

17:50.670 --> 17:54.197
if Cary and David Lee weren't
already making moves against me.

17:55.720 --> 17:58.939
I just want to know
where you'll land.

17:58.990 --> 18:02.073
I'm asking you
to land with me.

18:08.390 --> 18:10.733
Lucca Quinn isn't happy.

18:10.780 --> 18:13.032
She's downstairs, in a cubicle,

18:13.090 --> 18:15.342
being given grunt work,
when I think

18:15.390 --> 18:19.042
she is one of thesmartest
lawyers in the firm.

18:20.790 --> 18:22.269
You're asking me to promote her?

18:22.310 --> 18:24.449
I want to be at a firm

18:24.490 --> 18:27.402
that recognizes talent.

18:29.410 --> 18:31.970
All right,
let me take another look.

18:32.020 --> 18:35.888
And everybody hurts...

18:37.680 --> 18:40.717
Uh, would you excuse me
for just... just a minute.

18:40.770 --> 18:42.249
Mm.

18:53.740 --> 18:58.256
Everybody hurts

18:59.480 --> 19:03.007
Sometimes...

19:14.930 --> 19:16.750
Why don't you call him.

19:16.800 --> 19:18.495
Maybe it was just a friend.

19:18.540 --> 19:20.758
Or... an old flame

19:20.810 --> 19:22.619
or...

19:22.680 --> 19:24.545
I don't know.

19:24.590 --> 19:26.592
Why does it even matter?

19:26.640 --> 19:28.414
You're the one drinking.

19:28.470 --> 19:30.722
Maybe it doesn't.

19:30.770 --> 19:32.726
I mean, I didn't want
to... marry him.

19:32.780 --> 19:34.771
I don't want to...
tie him down.

19:34.820 --> 19:35.900
And you're married.

19:35.950 --> 19:39.738
[sighs]: I have issues
on this front.

19:41.090 --> 19:42.739
Husbands who screw around,

19:42.790 --> 19:45.395
who lie, who leave me in tears.

19:45.440 --> 19:47.658
You're not in tears now.

19:50.050 --> 19:52.052
You're right.

19:53.270 --> 19:54.441
I'm not.

19:54.490 --> 19:56.310
That's a sign of growth, right?

19:56.360 --> 19:58.749
Or something.Scar tissue.

19:58.800 --> 20:00.791
Maturity.

20:00.850 --> 20:02.579
Cynicism.

20:02.630 --> 20:04.359
You expect the
worst in people,

20:04.420 --> 20:07.890
you'll never be
disappointed.Right.

20:07.940 --> 20:10.022
You think this is
the worst of Jason?

20:10.070 --> 20:12.243
No. I didn't say that.

20:12.290 --> 20:15.020
He didn't promise you
anything, right?

20:16.990 --> 20:19.072
He didn't, did he?

20:19.130 --> 20:22.907
No, but I was becoming...

20:22.960 --> 20:24.951
invested.

20:25.000 --> 20:27.252
I liked it.

20:27.310 --> 20:29.608
I liked being with him.

20:29.660 --> 20:31.264
So why can't you
keep it up?

20:31.310 --> 20:32.652
Become another face
in his harem?

20:32.700 --> 20:34.656
Have fun.

20:34.710 --> 20:36.268
Start your own harem.

20:36.320 --> 20:39.619
When you stop having
fun, say good-bye.

20:40.890 --> 20:42.846
Oh, God, this isn't who I am.

20:42.890 --> 20:44.494
You don't know
who you are.

20:44.540 --> 20:46.622
No one knows
who they are.

20:46.680 --> 20:47.806
Talk to Jason.

20:47.850 --> 20:49.898
He likes you.

20:49.940 --> 20:52.852
And maybe it was
just a friend.

20:52.900 --> 20:54.982
Hey.

20:56.030 --> 20:58.203
Hey.[door closes]

20:58.250 --> 21:00.980
So, are we still on for tonight?

21:01.040 --> 21:04.476
Can I...
get back to you on that?

21:04.520 --> 21:05.600
Yeah. Sure.

21:05.650 --> 21:06.776
Grand jury stuff?

21:06.830 --> 21:08.513
Yes. That, too. Right.

21:08.570 --> 21:11.209
All right, so about
what I found out.

21:11.270 --> 21:12.692
Huh?

21:12.740 --> 21:13.786
Your daughter.

21:13.830 --> 21:15.559
Oh. Right.

21:15.620 --> 21:17.702
Dear God, I'm falling apart.

21:17.750 --> 21:20.218
All right, Genuine Thought--
it's big business

21:20.270 --> 21:22.534
in the fight against
student plagiarism.

21:22.580 --> 21:24.832
The software designers
have acknowledged

21:24.890 --> 21:26.972
they're having problems
with false positives,

21:27.020 --> 21:28.328
which is why the
company has settled

21:28.370 --> 21:29.496
a few lawsuits last year.

21:29.540 --> 21:31.849
Wait, false positives how?

21:31.890 --> 21:34.108
It might tag a section
as plagiarism when, in fact,

21:34.160 --> 21:37.800
it's just a phrase
in common usage.
For example,

21:37.860 --> 21:39.851
in one paper they flagged:
"there's not enough money

21:39.900 --> 21:42.505
to go around," or "according
to conventional wisdom"

21:42.560 --> 21:45.779
as plagiarized, when
in fact they're just
sort of clichs.

21:45.820 --> 21:47.811
Unoriginal, but
not plagiarized.

21:47.870 --> 21:50.259
So, what do I do?Well, you need
to find out

21:50.300 --> 21:51.824
what they're saying
is plagiarized.

21:51.870 --> 21:54.179
They won't tell me--
they say it breaks policy.

21:54.220 --> 21:56.268
They don't want more lawsuits.Okay.

21:56.310 --> 21:57.390
Great.

21:57.440 --> 21:59.351
Thanks.
I'll see what I can do.

22:00.840 --> 22:02.262
Hey...

22:02.320 --> 22:05.574
Everything is normal
here, right?

22:07.280 --> 22:08.929
As normal as it can be.

22:08.970 --> 22:10.881
Okay, so then we'll just...

22:10.930 --> 22:12.932
reschedule lunch.

22:14.420 --> 22:15.933
Okay.

22:15.980 --> 22:17.936
Hey, um,
Genuine Thought--

22:17.980 --> 22:21.370
they don't just have contracts
with colleges?

22:21.420 --> 22:23.888
No.So I could
submit something too?

22:25.990 --> 22:28.038
[indistinct conversations]

22:29.470 --> 22:32.906
I'm, uh, handing
the Harry redirect to Lucca.

22:32.960 --> 22:34.120
What?

22:34.170 --> 22:35.956
Why?

22:36.000 --> 22:38.389
Well, she knows the business.
And I want to encourage her.

22:41.920 --> 22:44.388
The first weekend of January,
12 people were shot

22:44.450 --> 22:46.395
within five blocks of my motel.

22:46.450 --> 22:49.886
By Monday, 75% of our guests
had checked out early.

22:49.930 --> 22:51.921
And eight parties
canceled their reservations

22:51.970 --> 22:53.710
the following weekend.

22:53.760 --> 22:55.182
Was that atypical?No, that's
been the pattern

22:55.240 --> 22:56.582
more than
the exception.

22:56.630 --> 22:59.542
Shootings,
check-outs, cancellations.

22:59.590 --> 23:00.932
But why are you
blaming Gloria's?

23:00.980 --> 23:02.584
Of the 700 crime guns

23:02.640 --> 23:04.369
traced back to Gloria last year,

23:04.420 --> 23:05.853
more than 200 were linked

23:05.900 --> 23:09.028
to shootings within a mile
of my motel.

23:09.080 --> 23:10.206
LUCCA:
Thank you, sir.
And I'm sorry.

23:10.250 --> 23:12.036
HOFF:
Isn't it true you've

23:12.080 --> 23:15.948
received more than 30
one-star Bed & Plate reviews?

23:16.000 --> 23:17.160
Yeah, but Bed & Plate
is a racket.

23:17.220 --> 23:18.869
[chuckles]
That I agree with.

23:18.910 --> 23:20.252
You don't
believe you have

23:20.310 --> 23:22.437
"beds the dead
would complain about"

23:22.480 --> 23:25.392
or "bathrooms reminiscent
of Soldier Field"?

23:25.440 --> 23:26.782
I look at the feedback,
try to fix

23:26.840 --> 23:28.171
any problems
that people point out.

23:28.230 --> 23:29.834
But don't you think
it's conceivable

23:29.880 --> 23:31.666
that those problems
are the direct cause

23:31.710 --> 23:34.099
of your drop in business,
not gun violence?

23:34.150 --> 23:37.187
No, the gun violence hurt my
business, so I had to cut back.

23:37.240 --> 23:38.400
Or were you cutting back
because you were

23:38.460 --> 23:40.109
saving up to buy another motel?

23:40.150 --> 23:41.879
Objection, Your Honor.
Foundation.ABERNATHY: Oh.

23:41.940 --> 23:43.282
I'll sustain that.I think I'm good here.

23:43.330 --> 23:44.581
I'll rest.

23:44.640 --> 23:47.108
Well, we seem to have

23:47.160 --> 23:50.334
a chicken and egg problem here,
and if you're

23:50.380 --> 23:51.938
trying to prove
causation,[phone dings]

23:51.990 --> 23:55.039
that is not good news.
Given that

23:55.080 --> 23:57.605
I cannot find enough evidence
to definitively rule

23:57.650 --> 23:59.470
that Mr. Dargis's
business suffered from

23:59.520 --> 24:00.737
gun violence specifically...

24:00.780 --> 24:03.123
Your Honor,

24:03.180 --> 24:05.478
before you rule...Ms. Lockhart, I feel like
I've been more than fair here.

24:05.530 --> 24:07.430
Absolutely.
Uh, but please,

24:07.480 --> 24:09.357
if you could just grant us
a brief recess,

24:09.400 --> 24:11.004
I believe we can offer you

24:11.050 --> 24:13.223
the definitive proof
that you're looking for.

24:13.270 --> 24:15.318
[indistinct conversations]

24:15.360 --> 24:17.225
Hotel owners,
restaurateurs,

24:17.280 --> 24:19.441
valet companies,
gift shops.

24:19.500 --> 24:22.014
They all say their business
